The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                               Corporate Briefs
                              
	 ABBs net profit for the financial year 2008 grew 11.33 per cent to Rs 547.41 crore against Rs 491.66 crore last year. The companys total revenue rose to Rs 6,967.45 crore from Rs 6,001.35 crore a year ago. ABB will pay a dividend of Rs 2.20 per share for the year ended December 31, 2008.                             
	 Areva T amp;D India has registered a 32 per cent increase in sales at Rs 2,641 crore for the year ended December 2008. The companys operating profit rose 16 per cent to Rs 405 crore over the previous year.                             
	 Nivea India Pvt Ltd has registered a growth rate of 129.3 per cent in 2008 after rejigging its distribution model at the beginning of the year. A number of product launches and a significant marketing spend enabled the company to cross the Rs 100-crore mark this year.                             
	 Mahindra Odyssea  part of the $6.7-billion Mahindra group  has launched fibreglass power boats measuring 22 feet and 33 feet, respectively, at the Mumbai International Boat Show. The Mahindra Odyssea 22 is priced Rs 9.90 lakh onwards.
